# Personal Website Template
 
A minimal personal website template inspired by [shud.in](https://shud.in/). Pure HTML and CSS — no frameworks, no build step, no dependencies.
 
## Files
 
| File | Page |
|---|---|
| `index.html` | About / home |
| `thoughts.html` | Writing list |
| `projects.html` | Projects |
| `post-template.html` | Individual post (copy per article) |
 
## Getting Started
 
1. Open each file and replace `Your Name` with your name in the `<title>` tag and `<h1>`.
2. Update the social links in `index.html` (GitHub, X/Twitter, LinkedIn).
3. Fill in your bio paragraphs on `index.html`.
4. Add your projects to `projects.html`.
5. Add posts to `thoughts.html` and create individual post pages from `post-template.html`.
## Adding a Post
 
1. Create a folder called `thoughts/` at the root of your site.
2. Copy `post-template.html` into it and rename it, e.g. `thoughts/my-first-post.html`.
3. Update the `<title>`, `.post-date`, `<h1>`, and article body in the copied file.
4. Add a corresponding entry to the list in `thoughts.html`:
```html
<li>
  <a href="thoughts/my-first-post.html">
    <span class="post-title">My First Post</span>
    <span class="post-date">2025.06.15</span>
  </a>
</li>
```
 
## Customization
 
All visual variables are defined at the top of each file's `<style>` block under `:root`:
 
```css
:root {
  --bg: #fcfcfc;       /* Page background */
  --text: #111;        /* Primary text */
  --muted: #666;       /* Nav links, dates, secondary text */
  --border: #e5e5e5;   /* Divider lines */
  --max-width: 680px;  /* Content column width */
  --side-pad: 2rem;    /* Horizontal padding */
}
```
 
Body copy uses `Georgia` (serif). Navigation uses the system sans-serif stack. To change fonts, update `--font-body` and `--font-ui` in each file's `:root`.
 
## Deployment
 
Any static host works — GitHub Pages, Netlify, Vercel, Cloudflare Pages, etc. No build step required; upload the HTML files directly.
 
**GitHub Pages quick start:**
 
```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "initial"
git remote add origin https://github.com/you/you.github.io.git
git push -u origin main
```
 
Your site will be live at `https://you.github.io`.
